<dl id="n37009p"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n37" href="#n37009p">N37 (VI.B.28A)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n37all.htm#n37009p"> 9(p)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 318 Patriotic stunts</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[<font size="-1">THE CIRCUS</font>]</font>: The circus season of 1876 was one of special features. That year was the centenary of the Declaration of Independance, and Barnum made the most of it. In the list of attractions were <mark>patriotic numbers</mark> that succeeded in stirring national enthusiasm &hellip; There was <font color="green">[inter alia]</font> a Goddess of Liberty, &ldquo;a Gigantic Live American Eagle,&rdquo; which was sheduled to &ldquo;hover overhead&rdquo; &hellip; <small> M.R. Werner, <a name="MRWP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#MRWP"><cite title="source">P.T. Barnum</cite></a> (1923) 318</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
